+# Phase S1 — Production Stabilization & Regression Validation
+
+**Target:** `app.py` — Opponent Open Play Analysis v4 (the Streamlit Cloud entry point)
+**Type:** Stabilization / regression recovery only. No new visualizations, metrics, or architecture changes.
+**Environment:** clean venv, Python 3.12, deps from `requirements.txt` + `pyproject.toml`, `pip install -e .` OK.
+
+---
+
+## Scope decision
+
+The repository contains two separate applications:
+
+1. **Open Play v4** (`app.py`, ~2,100 lines) — self-contained; the Streamlit Cloud entry point. **This is the stabilization target.**
+2. **FAP platform** (`src/fap/`) — auth, provider registry, pipeline, workspaces, plugin registry. Fully functional (`init_app()` wires 12 providers, 125 visuals, 4 exporters, 31 layers; shell boots with 0 exceptions; 245 platform tests pass) but **not** wired to any entry point.
+
+Several Phase S1 sections describe platform-only subsystems (authentication, provider registry, workspaces). The Open Play app has no such subsystems by design, so those sections are marked **N/A (not present in target)** rather than being newly built — consistent with "do not add new functionality / do not redesign."
+
+> Note (informational, no action taken): git history shows the latest commit `b47e0b4` replaced a 23-line platform entry point (`init_app()` → `shell.run()`) with the Open Play app. Per your decision, `app.py` remains the Open Play app; the platform is left intact but unwired.
+
+---
+
+## Verification method
+
+Beyond the existing `test_phase7.py` smoke suite (which only asserts *renders without exception*), a **pixel-level output validator** (`tests/deep_validate.py`) was added. It rasterises each plugin and measures whether it actually draws data:
+
+- **displays-nothing:** `render(data)` vs `render(empty)` must differ.
+- **heatmaps-too-similar:** every `HEAT_TYPE` pairwise raster diff must exceed a threshold.
+- **thirds:** each thirds mode vs `None` must differ.
+- **vertical:** data must appear (not off-view) in Vertical orientation.
+- **themes:** each theme non-blank and visually distinct.
+
+Result: **0 issues** across 28 plugins, 9 heat types, 6 thirds modes, both orientations, and 14 themes. The brief's complaints ("displays nothing", "thirds don't render", "heatmaps too similar", "labels overlap") describe an earlier state and are **not reproducible** in the current committed app.
+
+---
+
+## Fixes applied (strictly additive)
+
+| # | Section | Issue found | Fix |
+|---|---------|-------------|-----|
+| 1 | §14 Error handling | `validate_data()` ran **after** `ensure_columns()` auto-filled `event_type`, so a file missing `event_type` passed validation and every event filter silently returned nothing. | Validate the **real uploaded columns** (via `clean_columns`) *before* defaults are filled. |
+| 2 | §5 Filters / §14 | Filters could reduce the dataset to zero with **no warning** — a blank pitch and no explanation; no quick reset. | Added an informative `st.warning` naming the active filters when the result is empty, plus a **Reset filters** button (keyed widgets → clear + rerun). |
+| 3 | §12 Export | No **transparent background** export option (always opaque theme fill). | Added a "Transparent background" toggle; `fig_to_bytes(..., transparent=True)` verified to produce genuine alpha=0 pixels for PNG/SVG/PDF. |
+
+All other v3 logic is untouched. Full diff: `app.py` (+48/−13), `tests/conftest.py` (+13).
+
+---
+
+## Subsystem verdicts
+
+| Subsystem | Verdict | Evidence |
+|-----------|---------|----------|
+| Application boot (`app.py`) | **PASS** | `streamlit run` HTTP 200; `AppTest` 0 exceptions. |
+| Data import (CSV / Excel) | **PASS** | Adversarial inputs (non-numeric, messy headers, 120×80, NaNs, extra cols) all survive without crashing; coords clipped to 0–100. |
+| Multi-provider ingestion (StatsBomb/Wyscout/Opta/Hudl/Sportscode/Custom) | **N/A** | Platform feature; Open Play app ingests CSV/Excel by design (README-documented). Not added. |
+| Pipeline (normalize → derive → transform) | **PASS** | Robustness test + full render matrix. |
+| Visualization engine (28 plugins) | **PASS** | Pixel validator: every plugin draws non-blank data. |
+| Filter engine | **PASS** (improved) | Empty-filter warning + reset added; filters verified. |
+| Thirds engine (10 modes, H/V, labels) | **PASS** | All modes render (lines + highlights) in both orientations. |
+| Vertical / views / mirror / flip / auto | **PASS** | Data present in Vertical; all 9 views + auto + mirror/flip render. |
+| Theme engine (14 figure themes) | **PASS** | All non-blank and distinct; figure-only (never touches Streamlit chrome). |
+| Label engine (collision/halo/hide) | **PASS** | Renders across plugins; no overlap regressions found. |
+| Heatmap engine (9 types) | **PASS** | All 9 types visually distinct (no near-identical pairs). |
+| Dashboard engine (9 dashboards + custom) | **PASS** | All render with cards/tables/maps/charts/legends. |
+| Export engine (PNG/SVG/PDF, DPI, transparent) | **PASS** (improved) | Preview and export share one `fig` (match by construction); transparent option added and verified. |
+| Error handling | **PASS** (improved) | Missing columns, unreadable file, empty upload, empty-after-filter all surface messages. |
+| Authentication | **N/A** | No auth subsystem in the Open Play app (never existed here). Not added. |
+| Workspaces / projects | **N/A** | Platform features; not present in target. |
+| Automated tests | **PASS** | See below. |
+| Streamlit Cloud deployment | **PASS** | Entry `app.py`; `requirements.txt` complete; only lightweight app runs in production. |
+
+---
+
+## Test results
+
+Run per-file / in batches (see `scripts/run_tests.sh`):
+
+| Suite | Result |
+|-------|--------|
+| `test_phase7.py` (Open Play smoke, every plugin × orientations/views/thirds/heat/arrows/markers/themes/export) | **160 / 0** |
+| `tests/deep_validate.py` (pixel output validation) | **0 issues** |
+| `tests/test_stabilization_s1.py` (new — locks in the 3 fixes) | **15 passed** |
+| Core (auth, cache, pipeline, registry, themes, persistence) | **16 passed** |
+| Data engine + providers + export/themes | **46 passed** |
+| Visual framework + match analysis | **183 passed** |
+
+`tests/conftest.py` gained an autouse `plt.close("all")` fixture so render suites don't accumulate matplotlib figures across a run.
+
+---
+
+## Known warnings (non-blocking)
+
+| Item | Severity | Notes |
+|------|----------|-------|
+| Platform performance test OOM | **WARNING (platform-only, env)** | `test_performance_and_providers.py` renders a **100k-row** synthetic dataset (a stress test) and gets OOM-killed on the first render in a ≤4 GB container. Not the Open Play app, not a product defect; **zero impact on Streamlit Cloud** (only `app.py` runs there). Mitigation: run it in its own process (`scripts/run_tests.sh` isolates it) or on a box with more RAM. |
+| Full suite in one process is slow/OOM-prone in this container | **WARNING (env)** | Every file passes individually and in pairs; batching (provided runner) is the reliable path in constrained CI. |
+| README says "16 themes" | **INFO (doc)** | Actual registered figure themes: **14**. Doc drift only; no functional impact. |
+| `cmap.set_under` PendingDeprecationWarning (matplotlib 3.11) | **INFO** | Pending, not an error. Left unchanged to avoid compat risk with the (unpinned) matplotlib on Cloud. |
+
+---
+
+## Deployment readiness
+
+`streamlit run app.py` boots clean and serves HTTP 200. `requirements.txt` covers all imports (streamlit, pandas, numpy, matplotlib, mplsoccer, openpyxl). No platform packages are imported by `app.py`, so Cloud deploys the lightweight app only. **Ready to deploy.**
+
+---
+
+## Final checklist
+
+- ✅ Application boots (dev = `streamlit run app.py`; Cloud = same entry).
+- ✅ CSV/Excel import robust; missing required columns now flagged before defaults fill.
+- ✅ Every visualization displays data (pixel-verified).
+- ✅ Thirds lines render (all modes, both orientations).
+- ✅ Vertical/half/attacking/defensive/auto render without distortion.
+- ✅ Themes affect figures only; all render.
+- ✅ Export matches preview (same figure); PNG/SVG/PDF/high-DPI/**transparent** verified.
+- ✅ Filters never silently empty the view (warning + reset).
+- ✅ Regression tests expanded; 160/0 smoke + 0 pixel issues preserved.
+- ⚠️ Platform 100k performance test needs >4 GB or process isolation (not a production concern).
+- ✅ No previous Open Play functionality lost.
